title: Èyí làw?n ohun tí o lè ?e láti dènà ààrùn Mpox tó gbode kan báyìí
content: “Ohun ti a ni lati gba jum? bayii bi a se le pese alaafia fun aw?n eeyan to n fi ara w?n lel?, ati bi w?n yoo se ni anfani si aj?sara ati it?ju to peye.
title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: What is needed now is agreement on how to provide support for vulnerable people and ensure access to vaccines and adequate treatment.

title: Èyí làw?n ohun tí o lè ?e láti dènà ààrùn Mpox tó gbode kan báyìí
content: "Ti ikede ilu o fara? lori ilera  gbogbo eniyan ni irins? ti yoo pese iranl?w? fun DR Congo,  iy?n dara pup?..” ?j?gb?n Marks ni otit? ni pe aisan yii ti n tan kaakiri aw?n oril?ede to wa ni tosi bii bii Rwanda, Uganda ati Burundi ati pe eewu si Europe ati Am?rika si j? kekere.
title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: Professor Marks said public announcements of assistance for DRC are welcome; the outbreak is spreading to neighbours such as Rwanda, Uganda and Burundi and the risk to Europe and America is small.

title: Èyí làw?n ohun tí o lè ?e láti dènà ààrùn Mpox tó gbode kan báyìí
content: O fikun: “?kan ninu aw?n ba wa l?ru ni akoko yii ni pe a ko m? ?ru nnkan yii ati iye aw?n eeyan to n se ti a ko ti m?, nitori naa a ko m? otit? nipa iye eeyan to ti lugbadi aisan yii.” Arun Mpox j? aisan to n waye  nipas? kokoro-aarun monkeypox, ?m? ?gb? kana ni p?lu igbona(small pox).
title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: He added one worry is that we don't know how many cases remain undetected. Mpox is caused by the monkeypox virus, a member of the smallpox family."

title: Èyí làw?n ohun tí o lè ?e láti dènà ààrùn Mpox tó gbode kan báyìí
content: Ni ak?k?, ara ?ranko ni w?n ti ma n ko aarun yii si ara eeyan, to si n waye ni aw?n oril?ede Adulaw?p kan Ni aw?n agbegbe w?nyi, ?gb??gb?run aw?n aisan yii lo ti waye, ti ?p? eeyan si n padanu ?mi w?n l?d?dun- paapa aw?n ?m?de ti ?j? ori wa lab? ?dun m?dogun, to si j? pe aw?n ni w?n buru ju.
title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: Primarily the virus is transmitted from animals to humans in some African countries; in these areas thousands of infections occur and many people die each year — especially children under fifteen.

title: Èyí làw?n ohun tí o lè ?e láti dènà ààrùn Mpox tó gbode kan báyìí
content: Aisan yii pin si ?na meji, Ak?k? lo fa aisan to kal? ni gbogbo agbaye ni ?dun 2022, to tan ka oril?ede to le ni ?g?run un Ikeji, eyi lo lagbara ju to n waye ni  aringbungbun Afirika - clade 1b.
title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: The disease has two main clades: the one that caused the global outbreak in 2022 (which spread widely) is different from the clade circulating in Central Africa (clade 1b).

title: Èyí làw?n ohun tí o lè ?e láti dènà ààrùn Mpox tó gbode kan báyìí
content: Eyi lo wa l?yineyi  tuntun ti w?n s?s? ?awari laip? ni DR Congo , to n tan ka l? si Kenya, Rwanda, ati Uganda.
title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: This newer strain was recently identified in the DRC and is spreading to Kenya, Rwanda and Uganda."

title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: Mpox (monkeypox) can be transmitted from person to person.

title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: Typical symptoms include fever, sore throat, body aches, swollen lymph nodes and painful lesions. Once fever occurs, a rash begins and spreads from the face to the rest of the body, especially the hands and soles.

content_translation: Skin lesions may or may not be painful; they progress through stages before healing and often leave scars."

title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: Professor Marks said although the disease can be transmitted by close contact with an infected person, sexual intercourse is not necessarily the main driver of spread.

title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: This has caused spread across many African countries and has led to fatal outcomes among young men in South Africa."

title_translation: How to protect yourself from the current Mpox outbreak
content_translation: Dr Adeola Fowotade said two weeks earlier the DRC and Nigeria indicated they were ready to authorize vaccines they needed.
